# Project Structure

This is a monorepo project built with Next.js, React, and TypeScript. It uses Turborepo for managing the monorepo setup.

- **/apps**: Contains the main applications
  - **/web**: The main web application built with Next.js App Router
    - **/src/app**: Next.js app router structure (pages, layouts, etc.)
    - **/src/components**: React components used across the application
    - **/src/lib**: Utility functions and configuration
    - **/src/content**: Content-related data and utilities

- **/packages**: Shared packages used across applications
  - **/ui**: Shared UI components
  - **/utils**: Common utility functions
  - **/eslint-config**: Shared ESLint configuration
  - **/typescript-config**: Shared TypeScript configuration
  - **/bible**: Bible-related utilities and data

The project follows Next.js App Router conventions with a focus on Server Components where possible.
